org.mobicents.tools.sip.balancer

Class NullServerNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.mobicents.tools.sip.balancer.SIPNode
      • org.mobicents.tools.sip.balancer.NullServerNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<SIPNode>

    public class NullServerNode
extends SIPNode
    If your algorthm return an instance of this class the load balancer will not forward the request anywhere. For instance this is useful if you detected a call in unrecoverable state such as failure before ACK, then you would want to just drop the ACK.

    vladimirralev
